NBT staining was used to observe the effects of IOE on the infarction scale. As shown in 
 Fig. 2A, the infarct size reached up to 36.42Â±6.67% in the MI/R group. IOE (150, 300 and 600 mg/kg) significantly decreased the infarct size compared with the MI/R group (P<0.01). Furthermore, the activities of myocardial enzymes (LDH, CK-MB and AST) were significantly increased following MI/R injury compared with the Sham group, which further caused myocardial injury (P<0.01; 
 Fig. 2B-D). IOE attenuated MI/R injury through inhibiting the activities of myocardial enzymes in MI/R-IOE groups (P<0.01).
